Two faces: rare 4 m vertical pop (cross-cell) + frequent ~0.1 m horizontal stutter (same-cell, the 
~75% complaint). Fix candidates + the 3 already-reverted dead-ends + the non-debugger DBWIN capture 
method are in the handoff. Do AD-HOC (spike â†’ single fix phase), not a milestone. See 
`research/CONSULT-36-doorsnap-SYNTHESIS.md`.

- [login-music-miles-9.3v-research.md](login-music-miles-9.3v-research.md) â€” **RESOLVED 2026-06-18 
(`5a894d327`).** Login/character-select SCREEN music now plays. The 9.3v lead was a **red herring** 
â€” the bug was engine-side, not a Miles version difference: Miles' background IO thread re-opens 
the stream via our `AIL_set_file_callbacks` hook with an **empty filename** â†’ `TreeFile::open("")` 
returned NULL â†’ buffers never filled. Fix (`clientAudio/Audio.cpp`, gated 
`s_titleMusicStreamFix`): remember the real stream name + serve the empty-name re-open from it + 
track/seek read offset across re-opens + close prior handles (leak guard). Verified: plays 
start-to-finish, transitions to zone music, handles bounded. (9.3v was later adopted for x64 in 
`984afc073` for a **separate** in-game 3D-audio mixer bug.) Handoff kept as historical record.
