The downstream reliance is broader than visual collision: `CollisionWorld::canMoveOnFloor` converts 
`PWR_HitEdge` into `CMR_HitFloorEdge`, which path graph building uses to decide links. Suppressing a 
circle hit changes both runtime collision response and generated/dynamic path connectivity.
