docs\recon\10-dpvs-profiling.md:6:**Scenes:** Mos Eisley plaza (sparse outdoor), Mos Eisley starport 
(dense outdoor), walking (moving camera outdoor), cantina interior (POB indoor, sparse + dense)
docs\recon\10-dpvs-profiling.md:14:**Underlying data is scene-conditional `remove for outdoor, keep 
for indoor`** — DPVS occlusion culling flips sign between rendering topologies:
docs\recon\10-dpvs-profiling.md:16:- **Outdoor scenes:** `remove` (3/3 scenes voted independently). 
DPVS is net-negative. Cost grows with scene complexity (~940 µs/frame sparse → ~1,592 µs/frame 
dense); OFF wins median frame time by 3.3% to 9.1%.
docs\recon\10-dpvs-profiling.md:17:- **Indoor cells:** `keep` (cantina, validated across two scene 
densities + two camera anchors, n=3,724 frames). DPVS is net-positive. Tight geometry-dense spaces; 
DPVS saves ~742 µs CPU per frame; ON wins median frame time by 2.2%.
docs\recon\10-dpvs-profiling.md:19:**Applied decision: `remove` globally (Option α).** Architectural 
constraint identified during plan 10-06 execution: the `cullingParameters` bitmask in 
`RenderWorld.cpp` (lines 908 in `#ifdef _DEBUG` / 911 in release branch — same value via conditional 
compilation) feeds the single `ms_dpvsCamera->setParameters()` call at line 926. That camera is used 
for ALL rendering — indoor cells and outdoor scenes alike. There is no per-path code-level split 
available without a larger refactor to pass different culling parameters per cell context.
docs\recon\10-dpvs-profiling.md:22:- Outdoor magnitude × frequency: 0.94–2.13 ms gained × dominant 
playtime
docs\recon\10-dpvs-profiling.md:23:- Indoor regression × frequency: 0.66 ms lost × cantina/POB 
playtime (below human perception threshold)
docs\recon\10-dpvs-profiling.md:24:- Net: aggregate user experience improves; outdoor wins dominate.
docs\recon\10-dpvs-profiling.md:26:**Phase 11 reconsideration required.** When the D3D11 renderer 
lands, this trade may re-balance (cheaper draws may eliminate outdoor DPVS overhead OR eliminate 
indoor DPVS savings). Three options at that point:
docs\recon\10-dpvs-profiling.md:27:1. Keep Option α (remove globally) — if D3D11 numbers still favor 
outdoor
docs\recon\10-dpvs-profiling.md:28:2. Revert globally to `keep` — if D3D11 numbers flip outdoor to 
net-positive
