.planning/handoff\README.md:5:- 
[2026-06-20-cantina-door-snap-spike-START.md](2026-06-20-cantina-door-snap-spike-START.md) — **NEXT 
UP. Door-snap spike (v3.0 carry-forward VERIFY-01).** Root cause FOUND, no fix written. The cantina 
door-snap is a REAL pre-existing engine bug, NOT bitness/renderer (survives into x64 gl05 → 
falsified the "x64 fixes it" premise). Mechanism: footprint **circle** (~0.5 m) clips an 
**uncrossable floor-mesh seam edge** at the doorway → `PWR_HitEdge` → `CollisionResolve` rewind. Two 
faces: rare 4 m vertical pop (cross-cell) + frequent ~0.1 m horizontal stutter (same-cell, the ~75% 
complaint). Fix candidates + the 3 already-reverted dead-ends + the non-debugger DBWIN capture 
method are in the handoff. Do AD-HOC (spike → single fix phase), not a milestone. See 
`research/CONSULT-36-doorsnap-SYNTHESIS.md`.
