.planning/research\CONSULT-37-darkwall-falsify-frame.md:9:"The dark walls are 
**precalculated-vertex-lit** geometry. They get an empty dynamic light list (size 0). D3D9 renders 
them via a full-white ambient (1,1,1,0) × baked vertex colors; D3D11 lacks that path AND its asset 
world VS has no COLOR vertex input, so the baked lighting can't be read → too dark."
.planning/research\CONSULT-37-darkwall-falsify-frame.md:12:- D3D11: some building/wall geometry is 
**much too dark — but NOT pure black** (some light reaches it). Same geometry is correct in D3D9.
