codex
**Findings**

1. **NO-SHIP: Change A removes the radius constraint for every floor-only boundary hit where the 
center point succeeds.**  
   The proposed skip is at [.planning/research/CONSULT-41-doorsnap-fix.diff](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/.p
lanning/research/CONSULT-41-doorsnap-fix.diff:69). But `pathWalkCircleGetIds` first point-walks the 
center, then separately tests the radius circle against edges; those are intentionally different 
tests in [FloorMesh.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/c
ore/FloorMesh.cpp:2737) and [FloorMesh.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCol
lision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2826). `centerWalkResult == PWR_WalkOk` only proves the point 
stayed on floor, not that the 0.5m body can overlap an uncrossable edge. Real uncrossable edges are 
explicitly non-exitable in [FloorMesh.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedColl
ision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:1920), and overlapping one makes a circle not clear in [FloorMesh
.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:3
189). This change converts “center threads, body does not fit” into success.

2. **Blast radius is all footprinted creatures, not just the player.**  
   Caller chain: `pathWalkCircleGetIds` -> `pathWalkCircle` at [FloorMesh.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/
src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:2524) -> `Floor::canMove` at 
[Floor.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/Floor.cpp
:408) -> live collision in `CollisionResolve::findContactWithFloor` at [CollisionResolve.cpp](D:/Code
/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:779), 
and `CollisionWorld::canMoveOnFloor` at [CollisionWorld.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/
library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionWorld.cpp:2006). Footprints are allocated for any 
`SharedCreatureObjectTemplate`, not player-only, in [CollisionProperty.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src
/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionProperty.cpp:270) and [CollisionPrope
rty.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionPro
perty.cpp:290). The player flag is only name-derived at [CollisionProperty.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2
/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionProperty.cpp:278); Change A does 
not check it. Affected non-player movers: NPCs, creatures, pets, mounts/creature-based vehicles, and 
any scaled creature footprint.

3. **Downstream systems do rely on these contacts.**  
   Runtime collision turns `PWR_HitEdge` / `PWR_InContact` / center hit variants into floor contacts 
in [CollisionResolve.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/
core/CollisionResolve.cpp:790). Those contacts feed slide/contact history in [CollisionResolve.cpp](D
:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:4
46) and [CollisionResolve.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/sh
ared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:457), with rewind on resolved collision at [CollisionResolve.cpp](D:/C
ode/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/CollisionResolve.cpp:315)
. Path/can-move also depends on the same result: non-OK floor walk becomes `CMR_HitFloorEdge` in [Col
lisionWorld.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/Coll
isionWorld.cpp:2134), and dynamic path graph links are accepted with a 0.5m radius probe in [DynamicP
athGraph.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedPathfinding/src/shared/DynamicPat
hGraph.cpp:281). `FloorMesh::testConnectable` also uses `pathWalkCircle` directly in [FloorMesh.cpp](
D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp:3333).

4. **Highest-risk real geometry: narrow interior floor-only boundaries.**  
   The bad condition arises anywhere a walkable center passes near an uncrossable boundary edge: 
narrow POB/interior doorways, small gaps between floor cutouts, booth/bar/railing/pillar-base floor 
boundaries, and cell-floor edges where clearance is enforced by floor mesh rather than a solid 
extent. Static extents may still catch real rendered walls because `canMoveInCell` queries solid 
material first at [CollisionWorld.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollisio
n/src/shared/core/CollisionWorld.cpp:1621), but floor-only clearance boundaries are exactly what 
this code handles. Those are the dangerous cases: center can pass, radius should not.

**Verdict**

**NO-SHIP for Change A engine-wide.** The invariant is false: center-walkable does not imply 
radius-walkable.

Use a tighter semantic gate: suppress the contact only when the uncrossable boundary edge is proven 
to be a cross-floor/cross-cell portal seam, not a real clearance boundary. Exact condition should be 
equivalent to:

```cpp
centerWalkResult == PWR_WalkOk
&& edgeType == FET_Uncrossable
&& neighbor == -1
&& portalId == -1
&& edgeHasMatchingAdjacentPortalOrFloorSeam(edgeSegment, startCell, destinationCell, epsilon)
```

That last predicate must verify a nearby collinear/overlapping edge or portal on the adjacent 
floor/cell for the move. Without that seam proof, keep recording the circle contact.
